body:

Name: "Creative briefs"

Live URL: https://courses.thinkful.com/dm-branding-v1/checkpoint/4

Course code: dm-branding

Content:


    I don't believe the second question is properly asked based on the content.  Under Creative brief components, it lists 7 things "almost" all brands include.  It then details some include...  

However, in the question, 'project name' is part of the correct answer although it's mentioned as "helpful" in its subheading.

In addition, your provided template includes items that, per your answer, are optional.  If this is a fact, why is it included?  The student may infer that they are needed because your sample guide content and template includes it.  

Please:
a: only include in your template the items you deem as necessary
b: adjust the content to clearly define what components are "REQUIRED"
c:  Remove the ambiguous tone of the "OPTIONAL" content so there is no question to the learner what you want them to understand.
